visa_types.overview:
Due to the many possible requirements for different purposes of stay in Hungary, please read the information on the website of the General Directorate of Migration Affairs of Hungary: http://bmbah.hu/index.php?lang=en (http://bmbah.hu/index.php?lang=en)
Basic information:
- Applications for “D” visas are submitted at the Visa Application Center in Almaty and in Astana personally by the applicant. It is not possible to submit documents through a representative. All applicants over the age of 6 must submit their fingerprints.
- The consular fee is 110 (one hundred and ten) euros and service fee is 40 euro for all applicants (payment is accepted in tenge at the current exchange rate at the time of submission!).
- An application for temporary residence is considered by the General Directorate for Migration Affairs of Hungary up to 30 working days (study visas up to 15 working days), if necessary, this period can be extended up to 60 calendar days.
- If the application is approved, the Consulate General of Hungary issues a visa "D" for a single entry with a stay of 30 days in Hungary, during this period the applicant must obtain a residence permit card at the regional office of the General Directorate of Migration in Hungary.
- Depending on the purpose of your stay, please print out the corresponding application form (in English or in Hungarian) from the website of the General Directorate of Migration Affairs of Hungary. Frequently used forms:
Study:
Application form: Study Applocation Form
Appendix: Study Appendix 9.13
Work:
Application form: Work Application
Appendix: Work Appendix 9.6
Key Documents:
- The application form for the Hungarian visa "D" (application form) is completed in printed letters without gaps in English and signed personally by the applicant (in two places);
- 1 actual color photo taken no more than 6 months ago (3.5 x 4.5 cm) on a white background;
- Passport, which must have at least 2 free pages, its date of issue must not exceed 10 years and the validity of which expires no earlier than 3 months after the expiration of the requested period of stay;
- A copy of the applicant's passport (pages with personal data and Schengen visas);
- A document confirming the purpose of the trip (guest - a certified letter of invitation, educational - an invitation/certificate from an educational institution, family reunification: certificate of marriage, birth, etc.);
- Documents confirming the place of residence in Hungary;
- Documents confirming the availability of means of subsistence for the requested period of residence (for example: a current bank statement showing the availability of funds and their movement for the last 3 months; income statements (eg scholarships); guarantee obligations);
- Medical insurance policy valid for the entire period of stay;
- Documents confirming departure from the country at the end of the residence permit (repurchased air ticket, or availability of financial resources)
For details on additional documents in each case, see: http://bmbah.hu/index.php?lang=en (http://bmbah.hu/index.php?lang=en)

